Subject: [eVuln] eggblog Multiple SQL Injection & XSS Vulnerabilities


New eVuln Advisory:
eggblog Multiple SQL Injection & XSS Vulnerabilities
http://evuln.com/vulns/39/summary/bt/

--------------------Summary----------------

Software: eggblog
Sowtware's Web Site: http://www.epicdesigns.co.uk/projects/eggblog
Versions: 2.0
Critical Level: Moderate
Type: Multiple Vulnerabilities
Class: Remote
Status: Unpatched
Exploit: Available
Solution: Not Available
Discovered by: Aliaksandr Hartsuyeu (eVuln.com)
eVuln ID: EV0039

-----------------Description---------------
Most of user defined data isn't properly sanitized. This can be used to make any SQL query by injecting arbitrary SQL code (authorization or viewing blog and forum) or insert any javascript code (when posting new messages).

--------------Exploit----------------------
Available at: http://evuln.com/vulns/39/exploit/bt/


--------------Solution---------------------
No Patch available.

